<subSubSection id="C358655E86036B25FAF18689FA48F3FE" pageId="17" pageNumber="80" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586036B25FAF18689FA48F3FE" blockId="17.[1269,2256,2813,3173]" pageId="17" pageNumber="80">
Remarks. The investigated specimen is a very small juvenile and has a well preserved, seemingly planispiral apex. No muscle scar was observed. The specimen resembles the 
<typeStatus id="54F9887786036B25F9D087F3F9D5F435" box="[1544,1615,2951,2990]" pageId="17" pageNumber="80">type</typeStatus>
species in having a similar shell shape and concentric ornamentation. One small juvenile specimen with an asymmetric spiral apex is noticed. The placement of this specimen to 
<emphasis id="B936EAC786036B25F7DD8065F757F3A3" box="[2053,2253,3089,3128]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="80">'Lepetopsis'</emphasis>
is uncertain.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
